<h1 data-section-id="xocl15" data-start="2394" data-end="2426">Performance for Large Datasets</h1>
<p data-start="2428" data-end="2473">The algorithm has <strong data-start="2446" data-end="2472">linear time complexity</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="2475" data-end="2486">This means:</p>
<ul data-start="2488" data-end="2733">
<li data-section-id="leiype" data-start="2488" data-end="2557">
<p data-start="2490" data-end="2557">Doubling the amount of data approximately doubles the running time.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="ki6gum" data-start="2558" data-end="2603">
<p data-start="2560" data-end="2603">The recursive calls dominate the execution.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1lq7eaz" data-start="2604" data-end="2669">
<p data-start="2606" data-end="2669">The additional work of √n at each level is comparatively small.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="3q8h09" data-start="2670" data-end="2733">
<p data-start="2672" data-end="2733">The algorithm scales efficiently for large backup operations.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2735" data-end="2743">Example:</p>
<div class="TyagGW_tableContainer"><div tabindex="-1" class="group TyagGW_tableWrapper flex flex-col-reverse w-fit"><table data-start="2745" data-end="2946" class="w-fit min-w-(--thread-content-width)"><thead data-start="2745" data-end="2778"><tr data-start="2745" data-end="2778"><th data-start="2745" data-end="2760" data-col-size="sm" class="last:pe-10">Dataset Size</th><th data-start="2760" data-end="2778" data-col-size="sm" class="last:pe-10">Estimated Work</th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="2813" data-end="2946"><tr data-start="2813" data-end="2842"><td data-start="2813" data-end="2827" data-col-size="sm">1,000 files</td><td data-start="2827" data-end="2842" data-col-size="sm">1,000 units</td></tr><tr data-start="2843" data-end="2874"><td data-start="2843" data-end="2858" data-col-size="sm">10,000 files</td><td data-start="2858" data-end="2874" data-col-size="sm">10,000 units</td></tr><tr data-start="2875" data-end="2908"><td data-start="2875" data-end="2891" data-col-size="sm">100,000 files</td><td data-start="2891" data-end="2908" data-col-size="sm">100,000 units</td></tr><tr data-start="2909" data-end="2946"><td data-start="2909" data-end="2927" data-col-size="sm">1,000,000 files</td><td data-start="2927" data-end="2946" data-col-size="sm">1,000,000 units</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="relative h-0 self-end select-none"><div class="absolute end-0 flex items-end" style="height: 32.7969px;"><span class="" data-state="closed"><button aria-label="Copy table" class="hover:bg-token-bg-tertiary text-token-text-secondary relative z-10 my-1 rounded-sm p-1 transition-opacity group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:pointer-events-none group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:opacity-0"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-2df4e570.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></span></div></div></div></div>
<p data-start="2948" data-end="3010">The running time increases proportionally with the input size.</p>
